You're working on three strong themes:

**AI infrastructure** is your primary focus. Aether is an AI-native operating system written in Rust where AI is a first-class kernel subsystem with direct hardware access. MindWell and vivaha also sit in this space, though their specific purposes aren't fully documented.

**Developer tooling** is your second track. Friday, Friday V2, and Friday V3 are all in this domain—guidelines for engineering practices, and tools to make software engineers dramatically more capable. The progression across three versions suggests iteration on the core concept.

**Mental health** appears as a product application, primarily through MindWell, which offers anonymous storytelling, mood tracking, resource access, and community support with separate user and admin interfaces.

The themes overlap: MindWell combines developer tooling (the platform itself) with mental health as a domain. Aether anchors the AI infrastructure work at the OS level. Your portfolio suggests you're exploring how AI infrastructure, developer capabilities, and mental health intersect—though the integration points aren't explicit in the available evidence.

